{
  "name": "Villager Trading",
  "icon": "minecraft:emerald",
  "category": "lexicon:trading",
  "sortnum": 1,
  "pages": [
    {
      "type": "patchouli:text",
      "text": "$(li)There's 5 career levels that can be increased by trading. $(li)A full trading bar unlocks the next level of trades. $(li)Each profession has it's own offers. $(li)Professions are assigned to each $(l:creatures/human-villager)$(thing)Villager$() based on their job-site block. $(li)$(l:creatures/human-villager)$(thing)Villagers$() disable an offer after a few trades. But they activate their offers again, up to twice per day. $(li)They can have a maximum of 10 trades. Each level unlocks a maximum of 2 trades."
    },
    {
      "type": "patchouli:text",
      "title": "Economic",
      "text": "$(li)An sold out item gets a price increase when resupplied. If a player does not trade for a higher-priced item, the price is reduced the next time it resupplies. $(li)The $(l:brewing/effects#village_hero)$(thing)Hero of the Village effect$() temporarily reduces prices for the affected $(l:creatures/human-player)$(thing)Player$(). $(li)All price fluctuations affect only the first item involved in trade. $(li)A positive reputation is gained by curing $(l:creatures/undead-zombie_villager)$(thing)Zombie Villagers$(). $(br2)To cure a $(l:creatures/undead-zombie_villager)$(thing)Zombie Villager$(), splash it with a $(l:brewing/brewing)$(item)Splash Potion of Weakness$() and then feed it a $(l:rare/golden_apple)$(item)Golden Apple$()."
    },
    {
      "type": "patchouli:image",
      "images": [
        "lexicon:textures/pictures/trading_price_changes.png"
      ],
      "text": "> Price changes of cured villagers",
      "border": true
    },
